        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 6:42PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 642 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Alston, or 9 miles
southeast of Mount Vernon, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Uvalda, Alston, South Thompson, English Eddy, Center, Toombs Central,
Grays Landing, Rock Springs, Cedar Crossing, Charlotteville, and
McNatt Falls.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
